# Bench-runner output directory.
#
# `barista-bench run --output bench/runs/<run_id>/` writes per-run
# results.json + index.json artifacts here. By default these are
# **local only** — they reflect this developer's hardware tier and
# environment, not the canonical R-Bench-1/2/3 numbers the dashboard
# publishes. Checked-in runs are explicit exceptions: a small set of
# representative datasets that double as documentation + dashboard
# fixtures. Anything not explicitly opted in is ignored.

# Default: ignore everything under bench/runs/.
*

# Explicit exceptions — each checked-in run-directory must be listed
# here. Use this for runs that are referenced from public docs (e.g.
# the walkthrough writeup) or that ship as dashboard fixtures.
!.gitignore
!walkthrough-2026-05-18/
!walkthrough-2026-05-18/**
!walkthrough-2026-05-18-postfix/
!walkthrough-2026-05-18-postfix/**
